result.execSummary:
The defendant Mitchell W Rossow was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

timeConds.notes: The Defendant is to complete fifty (50) hours of community service during EACH year of his two (2) year term of probation for a total of one-hundred (100) hours with NO BUYOUT.

supervisions.notes:
The Defendant is to serve thirty (30) days in the Walworth County Jail with Huber privileges to commence on or before October 27, 2022 @ 8:00 a.m.  NOTE:  The defendant is to report to jail on time and with no detectable amount of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. Failure to comply will result in revocation of Huber for a period of five (5) days unless reinstated by the Court. 
------------------
IT IS HEREBY ORDERED THAT the defendant's excess Huber funds be applied to any & all outstanding Court obligations while serving his mandatory jail sentence.
